@ConcurrencyPractitioner : 

You don't need any permissions to start a PIP, but you do need permissions to post the PIP to Pulsar Github Wiki.
 
So you can just write down a PIP in gist and share it to dev@ mailing list. Any pulsar committer can help you re-post your gist to Pulsar wiki.

@joefk actually it was a part of the plan as @merlimat suggested :https://github.com/apache/pulsar/pull/538#discussion_r129182185
when we introduced this non-persistent feature to remove this config and created issue #596 to track it.
The main argument @merlimat had that isolating based on topic-types did not work well in jms/activeMQ and if n/w bandwidth is the concern then it can be achieved with namespace isolation without impacting other tenants. also, broker doesn't allow more than 1K pending publish req per cnx to throttle on each cnx. so, decided to remove this config once feature is matured and if it's not being used. However, we can also revert the change if this one is really needed.
@merlimat any thought?
